**Methodological Evolution**
- **Refinement of Elastic Filtering**: The previous iteration's elastic filtering criteria ($-20 < G_{VRH} < 200$ GPa) were tightened to strictly positive values ($0 < G_{VRH} < 200$ GPa) to eliminate unphysical negative shear moduli that previously introduced noise into the "Mechanical Viability" classifier.
- **Feature Engineering Update**: The `radius_ratio` was removed to resolve multicollinearity with the Goldschmidt tolerance factor ($\tau$), improving the interpretability of the stability model.
- **Pipeline Integration**: A two-stage hurdle model was implemented for electronic properties, replacing a single-stage regression approach to explicitly handle the zero-inflation of the band gap distribution.
- **Applicability Domain (AD) Constraint**: A One-Class SVM was introduced to filter candidates based on their proximity to the training distribution, preventing extrapolation into unphysical chemical spaces.

